{{Infobox person | name = Sven Thieme | image = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1968|02|08|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Namibia]]n | residence = [[Windhoek]]/[[Namibia]] | occupation = [[Businessman]] | salary = | networth = | spouse = | religion = | children = | parents = }}
'''Sven Thieme''' (born 8 February 1968) is a Namibian businessman.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.namibian.com.na/indexx.php?archive_id=88872&page_type=archive_story_detail&page=1291|title=Indongo, Pupkewitz and Sven Thieme receive Lifetime Awards|work=The Namibian|access-date=2018-01-08|language=en}}</ref> He is currently a chairman of [[Ohlthaver & List]] , the largest private company in Namibia.
==Education and training== Thieme attended [[Deutsche Höhere Privatschule Windhoek]] and graduated with the German ''[[Abitur]]'' in 1987. He graduated as an auditor in 1991 at the [[University of Cape Town]], [[South Africa]]. He completed his articles at [[Deloitte & Touche]] in Cape Town.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.namibian.com.na/indexx.php?id=15857&page_type=story_detail|title=Bringing culture back into business – An interview with NCCI Swakopmund's chairman Heinrich Hafen|work=The Namibian|access-date=2018-01-08|language=en}}</ref>
==Business career== He took over in 2002 after the death of his grandfather and company founder [[Werner List]] the CEO of Ohlthaver & List. He has worked since 1998 in the company; 2001 to 2002 as General Manager. He also sits several supervisory boards of subsidiaries. Previously, he was from 1994 to 1998 as an auditor for Deloitte & Touche in Luxemburg. In 2004, he was in charge of establishing the [[Development Bank of Namibia]]. In 2010 Thieme was in the Supervisory Board of the public broadcaster [[Namibian Broadcasting Corporation]]. Since 2014 he presided over the [[Namibia Chamber of Commerce and Industry]].<ref>{{cite news | title=NCCI elects new leadership | date=1 July 2015 | newspaper=[[The Namibian]] | url=http://www.namibian.com.na/index.php?id=125094}}</ref> He is considered as one of the most influential Namibians.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thevillager.com.na/articles/3157/2012-most-influential-personalities/|title=2012 most influential personalities|last=www.omalaetiit.com|first=Omalaeti Technologies, Namibia,|website=www.thevillager.com.na|language=en|access-date=2018-01-08}}</ref>
==Recognition== Thieme was conferred the [[Orders, decorations, and medals of Namibia|Most Distinguished Order of Namibia: First Class]] on [[Heroes' Day (Namibia)|Heroes' Day]] 2014.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Namibians honoured by President |newspaper=[[New Era (Namibia)|New Era]] |date= 28 August 2014 |url=http://www.newera.com.na/2014/08/28/namibians-honoured-by-president/}}</ref>
